meanings.definition: To swim faster than someone else.
meanings.sent1: During the race, Sarah outswims all her competitors effortlessly.
meanings.sent2: Michael Phelps always outswims his opponents in the pool.
meanings.sent3: The turtle challenged the rabbit to a swimming race, confident that he could outswim him.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to outswim her fears propelled her to success.
meanings.sent5: The cheetah outswims all other land animals with its incredible speed.

meanings.sent1: In the ocean, the dolphin outswims the shark with its agility.
meanings.sent2: The Olympic swimmer outswims all records with her incredible speed.
meanings.sent3: The little fish outswims the big fish in a surprising turn of events.
meanings.sent4: Her passion for swimming outswims any obstacles in her path.
meanings.sent5: The mermaid outswims all mythical creatures with her graceful strokes.
